Google LLM Status Check
-----------------------

I only mentioned Google briefly in yesterday's discussion about the state o=
f LLMs, noting that they likely had a cost advantage in infrastructure. Ind=
eed, Gemini is the cheapest option for a leading edge model, and has been f=
or a while; it also remains the only model with a massive context window. S=
ome users report that this doesn't work that well, but I've talked to other=
s who have had products unlocked by it; the broader point is that the most =
interesting and compelling aspect of Gemini does appear to be the API speci=
fically, and its exclusivity to Google Cloud Platform generally.

